  "prompt": "How do I know what he feels about me?",
  "response": "Understanding someone's feelings can be challenging, but there are several signs and strategies you can use to gain insight into how he feels about you:\n\n1. **Observe Body Language**: Pay attention to his body language. Open body language, consistent eye contact, and leaning in when talking are often signs of interest. \n\n2. **Listen to Communication**: Notice how often he initiates conversations and how engaged he is in your discussions. If he asks personal questions and remembers details, it\u2019s a good sign he cares.\n\n3. **Look for Consistency**: Consider how consistently he reaches out to you or makes an effort to spend time together. Frequent communication and invitations to join activities can indicate a deeper interest.\n\n4. **Evaluate His Actions**: Actions often speak louder than words. If he goes out of his way to help you or support you, it may be a sign of his feelings.\n\n5. **Seek Feedback**: If you feel comfortable, you can talk to him directly about your feelings and ask how he feels. Open and honest communication can clarify both of your feelings.\n\n6. **Gauge His Responses to Your Life**: See how he reacts to your successes and challenges. Someone who cares will typically show a genuine interest and concern for your well-being.\n\n7. **Consider His Interaction with Others**: Observe how he interacts with other people. Does he treat you differently from others? A distinct, more attentive approach can suggest special feelings.\n\n8. **Trust Your Instincts**: Sometimes, your intuition can tell you more than you realize. Reflect on your interactions and consider what your gut feeling tells you.\n\nRemember that everyone expresses feelings differently, so it\u2019s important to consider the overall context and not just isolated behaviors.",
